genresAdvancedInfo.name: musica goiana
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Musica goiana is a genre of music that originates from the Brazilian state of Goi√°s. It is characterized by its use of traditional Brazilian instruments such as the viola caipira and the accordion, as well as its incorporation of folk and country music elements. Musica goiana often tells stories of rural life and the struggles of the working class.
